by general relativity .

126
00:09:09,417 --> 00:09:14,538
So the fundamental difference 
between α(Newton) and α(Einstein)

127
00:09:14,538 --> 00:09:18,160
is that, using Newton's theory
of gravity,

128
00:09:18,160 --> 00:09:22,300
we have photons following 
curved trajectories

129
00:09:22,300 --> 00:09:24,586
in an Euclidean space. 

130
00:09:24,586 --> 00:09:27,603
In the framework of the general relativity theory

131
00:09:27,603 --> 00:09:31,893
we find that photons travel
along straight trajectories

132
00:09:31,893 --> 00:09:34,417
in a curved space,
in other words trajectories 

133
00:09:34,417 --> 00:09:37,040
that minimise the travel
time of photons,

134
00:09:37,040 --> 00:09:41,361
so what we call geodetics; and
these trajectories are those

135
00:09:41,361 --> 00:09:43,471
of shortest travel length
in a curved space.

136
00:09:43,471 --> 00:09:47,800
So we have two radically different
interpretations of gravitation, 

137
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:51,702
and this is what is crucial, and has given all
the legitimacy 

138
00:09:51,702 --> 00:09:55,243
to the general relativity theory,

139
00:09:55,243 --> 00:09:58,527
